## 4. Graph Neural Networks (GNNs)

### Message Passing Framework
The core operation in most GNNs:

```
For each node v at layer k:
  1. AGGREGATE: collect messages from neighbours N(v)
     m_v^(k) = AGGREGATE({h_u^(k-1) : u ∈ N(v)})
  2. UPDATE: combine with current state
     h_v^(k) = UPDATE(h_v^(k-1), m_v^(k))
```

### GNN Variants
| Model | Aggregation | Key Feature |
|-------|-------------|-------------|
| **GCN** (Graph Convolutional Network) | Normalised sum | Simple, scalable |
| **GraphSAGE** | Sample & aggregate (mean/max/LSTM) | Inductive (unseen nodes) |
| **GAT** (Graph Attention Network) | Weighted sum via learned attention | Differentiable importance weights |
| **GIN** (Graph Isomorphism Network) | Sum + MLP | Theoretically most powerful (WL test) |
| **MPNN** (Message Passing NN) | General message function | Molecular property prediction |

### Transductive vs. Inductive
| Type | Description | Use Case |
|------|-------------|---------|
| **Transductive** | Train and test on same fixed graph | Citation networks (Cora, Citeseer) |
| **Inductive** | Generalise to unseen nodes/graphs | Protein interaction, social networks |

