## 6. Graph ML Frameworks

| Framework | Language | Highlights |
|-----------|----------|-----------|
| **PyG** (PyTorch Geometric) | Python/PyTorch | Most popular, huge model zoo |
| **DGL** (Deep Graph Library) | Python/PyTorch/MXNet | Flexible message passing API |
| **StellarGraph** | Python/TensorFlow | High-level API, good docs |
| **NetworkX** | Python | Analysis only, no GPU training |

### PyG Example — GCN Node Classification
```python
import torch
import torch.nn.functional as F
from torch_geometric.nn import GCNConv

class GCN(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_features, num_classes):
        super().__init__()
        self.conv1 = GCNConv(num_features, 64)
        self.conv2 = GCNConv(64, num_classes)

    def forward(self, x, edge_index):
        x = F.relu(self.conv1(x, edge_index))
        x = F.dropout(x, training=self.training)
        return F.log_softmax(self.conv2(x, edge_index), dim=1)
```

