## 7. Graph Properties for Feature Engineering

| Metric | Level | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| Degree centrality | Node | Number of neighbours |
| Betweenness centrality | Node | Shortest-path broker importance |
| Closeness centrality | Node | Average distance to all nodes |
| Clustering coefficient | Node | Triangle density in neighbourhood |
| Modularity | Graph | Quality of community partitioning |
| Assortativity | Graph | Tendency of similar nodes to connect |
| Motifs / Graphlets | Subgraph | Small recurring structural patterns |

---

## 8. Graph ML for LLM-Enhanced Agents

- **GraphRAG**: GNN-based document retrieval with knowledge structure
- **LLM + KG reasoning**: LLM traverses KG via tool calls, GNN encodes subgraph context
- **Node2vec + LLM**: Use graph embeddings as additional features in LLM context
- **GNN as agent tool**: Expose GNN inference endpoint as callable tool in agent framework

